race.comment: ANGELIC BAROQUE (8) was prominent early off a low draw but weakened and dropped out when 7th over 520m at Wentworth Park in Grade 5 company. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. BUMPY BLUE (2) has been below best and missed the frame last couple, finishing 6th (22.89) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Has won here at this journey. Has ability and is one of the better chances. LIVIA SOPRANO (1) produced a moderate run last time when seventh at this track over 388m behind Cawbourne Spade (23.16) in a Mix 2/3. The form from her last run stacks up well. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. TILLY'S ON TOP (7) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.
